\begin_layout Section
Introduction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The aim of the project is to develop a digital system for an electric car-sharin
g company, called PowerEnjoy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Document Conventions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Headquarter: it is the head office of Power Enjoy Society.
 There are both call centre and employees who deal with taking care of cars.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Emergency number: number labeled in the car that the user can call in case
 of any emergency.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Call center: a large office in the Headquarter in which a Power Enjoy's
 employees provide information or service to its customers by phone when
 they call the emergency number.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Car: it is an electric car registered in the Power Enjoy Company.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
User: he/she is a client of the service.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
All Credentials: these are all information about the user that the system
 needs.
 The information contains name, last name, social security number, home
 address, email and drive license number.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Login Credentials : these are email and password that the user has to provide
 at the login phase.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Check message: is the message that the system sends to the user if he/she
 fills out the form, during the registration phase, with information that
 are not correct.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Reservation message: is the message that the system send to the user who
 has just reserved a car.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
State: is the state of the car which includes the level of battery, position
 and the number of passengers.
 If the vehicle is reserved or used the state will be associated with the
 respective user.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Special Parking Areas : these are special areas with plugs for the car.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Safe Areas: these are the area that determinate the boundary domain of our
 service.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Unsafe Areas: all the areas that are not safe / this term includes everything
 that is not in the safe areas.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Unsafe fine: the fine that the user has to pay if he/she left the car in
 an unsafe area.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Time Expire: the period of time from reservation that the user has to get
 to the car without paying the expire time fine.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Expire time fine: fine that the user has to pay if, after an hour from the
 reservation, he/she doesn’t reach the car.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Money saving option: if the user enables the money saving option, he/she
 can input his/her final destination and the system provides information
 about the station where to leave the car to get a discount.
 This station is determined to ensure a uniform distribution of cars in
 the city and depends both on the destination of the user and on the availabilit
y of power plugs at the selected station.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Final destination: the destination that the user enters in the navigator
 once he/she has hired a car.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Symbolic amount: money that the user has to pay once he/she registered,
 the value is of one cent .
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Money saving option: if the user enables the money saving option, he/she
 can input his/her final destination and the system provides information
 about the station where to leave the car to get a discount.
 This station is determined to ensure a uniform distribution of cars in
 the city and depends both on the destination of the user and on the availabilit
y of power plugs at the selected station.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Types of discount:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
If the system detects the user took at least two other passengers onto the
 car, the system applies a discount of 10% on the last ride.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If a car is left with no more than 50% of the battery empty, the system
 applies a discount of 20% on the last ride.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If a car is left at special parking areas where they can be recharged the
 system applies a discount of 30% on the last ride.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
