\begin_layout Subsection
Product functions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Functional requirements
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subparagraph
Employee:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[G1] Allows the employee to log in in the system, by app or website:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The system must be able to check if the credentials provided are correct.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
[G2] Allow the employee to put the car in unavailable mode.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The employee must be able to set the state of the car in unavailable mode,
 in order to take car of the car.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The employee must be able to release the car, to make it available by all
 users.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
[G3] Allow the employee to know what car he/she has to take care.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
In the headquarters, the employee will receive a list of car which he/she
 has to take care and the daily colleague.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
That list is continuously being update according to the daily activity delivered
 by the system.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
